** Software Developer **

At Aurion, we’ve been the trusted people and payroll partner of Australian
businesses for over 35 years. We are committed to delivering exceptional
people and payroll solutions to _ make life work better _ for our customers.

Our powerful, industry-leading people and payroll software supports hundreds
of Australian businesses to have simple, effective solutions to meet their
unique and complex requirements.

As an Aurion Software Developer, you will be passionate about leveraging
technology to deliver tangible business outcomes for our customers. We are
looking for our next innovative thinker who is looking to bring the latest
development trends and design patterns to deliver elegant people and payroll
solutions.

Working as a part of our T50 Development team, you will be working with our
Software Operations department to deliver the next version of our industry-
leading Aurion people and payroll software.

** Responsibilities **

  * Collaborate as a part of a multi-skilled team to deliver software solutions to the business 
  * Deliver high quality working code (frontend and server side) using modern design patterns, techniques and processes in an Agile Development environment 
  * Facilitate a Test-Driven development approach across the team 
  * Work on all aspects of the software delivery process, from requirements through to design and delivery to implementation and support 
  * Coordinate and work closely with all development teams to deliver all stages within the project, from the initial prototype through to production releases 
  * Mentor and teach other developers within the team, through code reviews, pair programming and other more formal formats 

** Skills and experience **

  * Preferable development skills in TypeScript, Node.js, Javascript or Python 
  * Web technologies and frameworks such as React (preferred), Vue or Svelte 
  * Server-side business transaction experience 
  * Web Services, including RESTful APIs 
  * Experience with Cloud Platforms (AWS preferred) 
  * Previous experience of building large, custom-built micro-services based applications 
  * Understanding of Agile Development practices, specifically Scrum or Kanban 
  * Practical experience with unit testing frameworks and automated testing tools 

** Benefits of joining our team **

  * Training, guidance, and assistance provided to further your career development 
  * Competitive salary package 
  * Flexible working arrangements 
  * Great team culture 
  * Future career opportunities in a thriving tech business 
  * Employee benefits including flexible work arrangements, health checks, employee assistance program and much more! 
  * The security of joining a trusted and established Australian brand 

Our people are integral to our success. As part of the Aurion team you can
look forward to receiving strong support to progress in your role and enjoy a
friendly, respectful, collaborative culture. At Aurion, fantastic work is done
by fantastic people, and you have the opportunity to work with true industry
experts.

Rated an ** HRD Employer of Choice for 3 years in a row ** , we offer a range
of industry-leading benefits, including:

  * Salary sacrificing options 
  * Learning and career development opportunities 
  * Hybrid working arrangements available 
  * Generous parental leave, career breaks, study leave and unpaid leave 
  * Recognition and rewards program 

Diversity and inclusion is strongly supported at Aurion from our Leadership
Team down, who reflect the company’s values and promote our ‘One Team Aurion’
culture. People of all nationalities, gender identities, and cultural
backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, are
encouraged to apply.

We also encourage individuals with disabilities to apply. We will provide the
right physical environment and support for anyone to enjoy equal access to the
right employment opportunities, from the interview process and beyond.

If this job interests you but you aren’t certain if you meet all the
requirements, we encourage you to still apply.

We’re excited to welcome our new team member. If this opportunity sounds right
for you, please apply through Seek today.

